Traditional rulers, stakeholders, women and youth groups from across the three senatorial districts of Kogi State have declared support for the re-election of Gov. Yahaya Bello come November 2. The endorsements of Bello which held at the Government House, Lokoja, began on Monday with people of Kogi Central, while Kogi West and East took their turns on Tuesday and Wednesday respectively. The traditional rulers, youth/women groups and other stakeholders from the three senatorial districts said the governor had done well in his first term and deserved a second term to enable him consolidate on the gains he had recorded so far. The Obaro of Kabba, Oba Solomon Dele Owoniyi, said the governor had done a lot in his first term and there was no need to “change horse in midstream.” Oba Owoniyi listed some of Bello’s achievements to include establishment of the multi-billion-naira Omi Rice Processing Mill, Isanlu Water Project, ongoing expansion of Isnalu General Hospital and provision of drugs to all hospitals/clinics in the area. He also lauded the governor for accommodating youths and “children of nobody” in his government while thanking him for being a detribalised leader. Responding, Gov. Bello assured the people of the state of a better deal if elected as governor for a second term come November 2, saying that he would not disappoint them. 2019: Kogi West endorses Buhari, adopts Bello Oba Owoniyi enthroned as 44th Obaro of Kabba Yahaya Bello: Unveiling the man who took a short walk to Lugard House Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin